page.title: 07LOCAL NEWS -II MAY 1985
page.content:
CONSERVATION -"RUBBISH DUMP ?" - An area of woodland which is pat of the North Downs and described as "of prime importance" is being ruined by motorcyclists and rubbish dumpers. The wooded area, mostly yew beech and chesnut trees, is losing its topsoil due to motorbike scrambling.
SUMMER SESSION OF FESTIVALS AND CARNIVALS being planned.
A NEW OFFICE BLOCK - The five storey building is to be on an "island" site near Maidstone Prison. The owners, Municipal Mutual Insurance, expect to house their life insurance department at the hexagonal building.
FLOWER FESTIVAL - United Reform Church
KENT MP WANTS SUNDAY TRADING
